  "prompt": "Do entrepreneurs leave US to find better opportunities abroad?",
  "response": "Some entrepreneurs do choose to relocate or expand their businesses internationally for various reasons:\n\n1. Lower operating costs\n- Cheaper labor\n- Lower taxes\n- Less regulatory burden\n\n2. Emerging market opportunities\n- Faster growing economies\n- Less competition\n- Untapped markets\n\n3. Specific incentives\n- Startup-friendly visa programs\n- Government grants\n- Technology/innovation zones\n\n4. Global talent access\n- Diverse skill pools\n- Lower recruitment costs\n- International networking\n\nExamples include:\n- Silicon Valley entrepreneurs moving to places like Singapore, Berlin, Tel Aviv\n- Tech startups exploring markets in India, Southeast Asia\n- Founders seeking more supportive entrepreneurial ecosystems\n\nHowever, many entrepreneurs still prefer the US due to:\n- Strong venture capital infrastructure\n- Advanced technological ecosystem\n- Large domestic market\n- Established innovation culture\n\nThe trend varies by industry and individual circumstances, but some entrepreneurs do seek opportunities abroad.",
